La crise mondiale de Covid-19 nous a amenés à repenser nos procédures et nos services pour limiter les risques de contamination. Nous avons établi pour vous une liste de tout ce qu’il y a à savoir afin de voyager en toute sérénité.

Air Tahiti Nui met votre bien-être au cœur de ses priorités.

Réglementations et conditions d’entrées dans chaque pays, mesures barrières, masques obligatoires… bien se préparer c’est voyager en sécurité. ✈️

#staystrong #wellmakeitthrough #weareaviation #airtahitinui #theislandsoftahiti #betterdaysahead #instaaviation #instatravel #instapassport #freedom #fly #restart

The global Covid-19 crisis has led us to rethink our procedures and services in order to limit the risk of contamination. 

Air Tahiti Nui puts your well-being at the heart of its priorities.

Regulations and entry conditions in each country, barrier measures, mandatory masks .... We have created this checklist to prepare you for a safe trip with us.

#staystrong #wellmakeitthrough #weareaviation #airtahitinui #theislandsoftahiti #betterdaysahead #instaaviation #instatravel #instapassport #freedom #fly #restart

node.text:
Air Tahiti Nui employees have taken part in the #DontRushChallenge game, which is a rising trend across social media.
We are showing you today their version of this challenge which highlights their good humor while waiting to welcome you again aboard ✈️
#StayHome #StayStrong #Wewillbebacksoon 
Thank you to everyone who participated in this worldwide phenomenon for our greater pleasure 😊

Production: Teiva Ribet et Vaiatua Van Bastolaer

Musical Creation: Mevina Liufau « Don’t rush and fly with us »

Assistants: Cliff Loussan et Iritia Taputu

Cabin Crew and Technical Staff in order of appearance: 
Vaiatua, Cliff, Teura, Maheata, Hinerava, Iritia, Ahurau, Isabelle, Vaitiare, Vairoa, Vanessa, Stéphanie Moanatea Tavahi et Maïli, Cathy, Heiti, Poerangi, Céline, Jefferson, Matahiarii, Mina, Evans, Vaiana, Gaëlle, Audrey, Vetea, Raiarii, Déryl, Isabelle, Heirangi, Sandrine, Tepaeva, Erika, Terupe, Joël, Mariko, Manoa, Kohi, Tifany, Bastien, Stephen, Kathlyn, Rainui, Matangi, Taraina, Ludovic.

node.text:
Our passion drives us every day to offer you high quality services and a unique flying experience.  ✈️

Over the past few months, the work of our teams has been rewarded with many prestigious awards internationally recognized:

✔️Air Tahiti Nui has thus been elected "Five Star Major Airline" in the APEX Official Airline Ratings.

✔️It was also recognized as "Best Airline in the South Pacific" and "Best Leisure Airline" during the last Global Traveler Awards.

✔️The Air Tahiti Nui Wine List also stood out at the Cellars in the Sky 2020 competition, allowing it to win no less than three gold medals and a jury award!

We are honored to receive such awards. And traveling with you is a great joy. Thanks to you, we surpass ourselves every day! We do everything we can to make sure you experience authentic adventures and unforgettable trips. Māuruuru.

node.text:
Te Aito and Super Aito, two exceptional va'a (Polynesian canoe) races bringing together local and foreign rowers for a thrilling event ! 

The Polynesian culture is celebrated, the friendly atmosphere and the incredible landscapes are always part of the event... A traditional sport that is becoming more and more popular internationally 🌎 and offers us every year impressive performances during the competitions!

The 33rd edition of Te Aito starts today in Tahiti and the 29th edition of Super Aito will be held on August 21 in Rangiroa.

Air Tahiti Nui to connect New Zealand with Key Trading Partners !

Last Thursday, Air Tahiti Nui successfully operated its first CARGO flight between Polynesia and New Zealand. ✈️

Following a bid to the New Zealand Ministry of Transport, the Polynesian airline will now operate weekly cargo rotations. This operation aims at facilitating trade between the two countries and will allow the weekly transport of 24.2 tons of New Zealand products to Polynesia, the United States and Europe.

🎥 @feature.nz
